The equation of the line passing through $(19,99)$ and the origin is $y = \frac{99}{19}x$. This line intersects the side of the parallelogram with endpoints $(10,45)$ and $(10,114)$ at the point $(10, 45 + \frac{99}{19} \cdot (-9)) = (10, -36)$. Since the line through the origin cuts the parallelogram into two congruent figures, it must pass through the midpoint of the side with endpoints $(28, 153)$ and $(28, 84)$, which is $(28, \frac{153+84}{2}) = (28, 118.5)$.

Thus, the slope of the line through the origin is $\frac{118.5}{28} = \frac{79}{16}$, and $m+n = \boxed{95}$.

