Then $OA = OB = y,$ so by the Pythagorean Theorem, $AB = 2y.$  Hence, the circumference of the circle of contact is $2 \pi y.$

As the cone rolls one full revolution, the point of contact travels a distance equal to the circumference of the base, namely $2 \pi r.$  Hence, as the cone rolls 17 times, the point of contact travels a distance of $34 \pi r.$  But the point of contact also travels a distance of $2 \pi y$ along the circular path of radius $x,$ so
\[2 \pi y = 34 \pi r - 2 \pi x.\]By similar triangles, $\frac{x}{r} = \frac{h}{y},$ so $x = \frac{hr}{y}.$  Substituting, we get
\[2 \pi y = 34 \pi r - 2 \pi \cdot \frac{hr}{y}.\]Then $y^2 = 17r^2 - hr^2,$ so
\[\frac{h}{r} = 17 - \frac{y^2}{r^2} = 17 - \frac{17r^2 - hr^2}{r^2} = 18 - \frac{h}{r}.\]Hence, $\frac{h}{r} = 6 \sqrt{2},$ so $m + n = \boxed{008}.$

