[/asy]

The area of the shaded region is then equal to the area of the larger circle minus the sum of the areas of the three regions.

The area of the larger circle is $\pi(6^2) = 36\pi.$

The three regions are congruent, so it suffices to compute the area of one of them.  This area is equal to the area of a sector of $60^\circ$ minus the area of an equilateral triangle with side length 2.

[asy]
size(100);
import graph;
filldraw(Circle((0,0),2),mediumgray);
filldraw(Circle((-1,0),1),white);
filldraw(Circle((1,0),1),white);
draw((0,0)--(1,0),dashed);
