The area of the sector is $(60^\circ/360^\circ) \cdot \pi(1^2) = \pi/6,$ and the area of the equilateral triangle is $(\sqrt{3}/4)(2^2) = \sqrt{3}.$  Hence, the area of one of the three regions is $\pi/6 - \sqrt{3}.$

Therefore, the area of the shaded region is
\[36\pi - 3 \cdot \left( \frac{\pi}{6} - \sqrt{3} \right) = \boxed{30\pi + 3 \sqrt{3}}.\]

